The paper discusses improvements to the AMR parsing task using machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Specifically, the paper focuses on using the smatch scoring script and neural translation models to improve accuracy. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of rule-based classifiers and ensemble methods, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of character-level neural translation, which is a sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of parsing accuracy, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
